summary: Ohh ok. Unintelligent rambling coming up:  I think I might know why movies like Sonic constantly fail but Detective Pikachu ...
body:
Ohh ok. Unintelligent rambling coming up:

I think I might know why movies like Sonic constantly fail but Detective Pikachu  thrive so well (besides because the people who made them are fans and not money grabbing corporates)

The universe!

Ok hear me out. Detective Pikachu is set not in our world but in the pokemon world. They didn’t just plop Reynoldschu in to today and say “You live here now. go save us” they made a living, breathing, city full of Pokemon that have existed since forever and thus the writers have everything to play with and it will make sense. Pokemon smoking? Sure. A trainer doing 25 to life in Prison because a gengar framed him. Funny but ok! The rules can be up to you.

This works with Game of Thrones, Dc movies and even Alita: Battle angel. They already exist and we’re just visiting their home for the day.


But with Sonic, they Stuck them on our time line which now means they can only live by our rules and because of this we are going to be annoyed when they break our rules. Anything unrealistic he does in our world will be take people out of the experience.

Hedgehog with teeth, Stopping time long enough for you to play drums with rockets, a guy with a kid in a bag but no one does anything about it….no no no.


I don’t know where i go with these long rants but stop setting already fictional worlds in to our world. Sonic has a world, set the movie there. Let us visit Sonic for the day don’t bring him to us.
